\f0\b\fs52 \cf0 Conchiglie al Forno with Mushrooms and Radicchio\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl240\ql\qnatural

\f1\fs32 \cf2 Serves:  
\b0 \cf0 4\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs44 \cf0 Ingredients\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl400\ql\qnatural
\ls1\ilvl0
\f1\b0\fs42 \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}6 ounces {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/shiitake/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 shiitake mushrooms}}, cleaned and trimmed\
{\listtext	\'95	}8 tablespoons (1 stick) {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/butter/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 unsalted butter}}\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 teaspoon kosher salt\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 cups (2 medium heads) finely shredded radicchio\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 1/2 cups {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/cream/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 heavy cream}}\
{\listtext	\'95	}1/2 cup freshly grated {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/parmigiano-reggiano/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 Parmigiano-Reggiano}} (1 1/2 ounces)\
{\listtext	\'95	}1/2 cup coarsely shredded fontina (1 1/2 ounces)\
{\listtext	\'95	}1/2 cup crumbled {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/gorgonzola/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 Gorgonzola}} (3 ounces)\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 teaspoons ricotta\
{\listtext	\'95	}6 leaves fresh sage, chopped (see note)\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 pound imported conchiglie rigate (pasta shells)\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs44 \cf0 Directions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa140\ql\qnatural

\f1\b0\fs42 \cf0 Preheat the oven to 500 degrees F.\
Bring 5 quarts of salted water to a boil in a stockpot.\
Remove the stems from the mushrooms and reserve for another use. Slice the mushroom caps about 1/4-inch thick. Heat 6 tablespoons of butter in a large skillet; add the mushrooms and 1/4 teaspoon salt. Saute over medium heat, stirring frequently, until they are cooked through, 3 to 5 minutes.\
In a large mixing bowl, combine the mushrooms, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/radicchio/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 radicchio}}, cream, cheeses, sage, and remaining salt.\
Parboil the pasta shells for 4 minutes; drain and add to the ingredients in the mixing bowl. Toss to combine.\
Divide the pasta mixture among 6 to 8 individual, shallow, ceramic gratin dishes (1 1/2 to 2 cup capacity). Dot with the remaining 2 tablespoons of butter and bake until bubbly and brown on top, about 7 to 10 minutes.\
Note: In the absence of fresh sage, do not substitute dried. As a substitute, choose one of the following: 1 tablespoon coarsely chopped fresh {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/tarragon/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 tarragon}} OR 1 teaspoon fresh thyme leaves OR\
8 leaves fresh {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/rosemary/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 rosemary}} OR 1/4 teaspoon {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/fennel-seed/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 fennel seed}}\
Note: You may garnish with fresh {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/italian-parsley/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 Italian parsley}}, but do not cook the parsley in the pasta.}